To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of any complaint or report precipitating the February 8, 2024, suspension (or other action) against Tiger Craven-Neeley, as reported by the San Francisco Chronicle at https://www.sfchronicle.com/bayarea/article/woke-kindergarten-schools-teacher-on-leave-18655992.php.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

communications.subject: Mike Teller  Public Records Request :: P003391-020724
communications.communication:
--- Please respond above this line --- 
 Public Records Request: P003391-020724 
 
   
  
 RE: PUBLIC RECORDS REQUEST of February 07, 2024 Reference # P003391-020724 Dear Mike, Request status: HOLD pending modification Your request as it stands is overly broad and unduly burdensome.Your request lacks a reasonable timeline (like one specific week). Your request lacks specificity (specific names). Your request lacks a keyword for a search. There are over 21,000 employees at the University of Wisconsin Madison and on any given day many may email a business for a variety of reasons. If you are seeking records you will know the subject for a keyword search. The law does not allow us to guess at what record(s) you are looking for. If I have not heard back from you by 2.15.24 your request will be closed as abandoned. You may always make a new request. 
Julie Laundrie Public Records Custodian Office of Compliance University of Wisconsin-Madison
